==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mystification
<hw>Mys`ti*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mystification</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of mystifying, or the
state of being mystied; also, something designed to, or that does,
mystify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The reply of Pope seems very much as though he had been playing
off a <qex>mystification</qex> on his Grace.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mystificator</ent>⟦br⟧
